node.contents: Hi guys! I've been reading SIv4.x docs and found that a RedisLockRegistry was added. As far as I can see, this Lock may solve this problem. Reaper and Aggregator must use this RedisLockRegistry to avoid locks, am I right?

astNode.text: Hi guys! I've been reading SIv4.x docs and found that a RedisLockRegistry was added. As far as I can see, this Lock may solve this problem. Reaper and Aggregator must use this RedisLockRegistry to avoid locks, am I right?

node.contents: This is strange; I don't see any opportunity for the lock to be left locked; the `RedisLockRegistry` won't help - that's for when using multiple application instances and a shared group store.
